  levelNumber: 5
  levelName: Uxbenka
  location: Toledo, Belice
  levelDescription: "The forest keeps its ruins close \u2014 but the past still breathes
    beneath the leaves.\n\nHidden among mist-covered hills, Uxbenk\xE1 is one of
    Belize\u2019s oldest known Maya centers, dating to around 250 BC.\nIts plazas
    and carved stones speak of an early kingdom tied to trade routes between the
    Guatemalan highlands and the coast.\n\nHere, leaders ruled from terraced hills,
    surrounded by farmers and artisans.\nThough small compared to later cities, Uxbenk\xE1\u2019s
    stelae bear the glyphs of power and ancestry, linking it to the greater Maya
    world."
